The paper discusses a deep learning framework for constrained clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the use of side information such as continuous values and high-level domain knowledge, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper explores advances in constrained clustering, which could also relate to social and information networks (cs.SI).
